notesStmt.note: One singleton missing between folios 10 and 11; one leaf missing between folios 18 and 19
Folio 205 consists of a seventeenth- or eighteenth-century noted chant and five fragments of a glossed fourteenth-century legal text pasted onto cardboard

Faye, C.U., continued and edited by W.H. Bond, Supplement to the Census of Medieval and Renaissance Manuscripts in the United States and Canada (New York: Bibliographical Society of America, 1962), p. 469, no. 19.

msContents.summary: This large Antiphonal was produced around 1500 in Spain. It retains its original covers, complete with tooled leather, central and corner bosses, and corner pieces.

msItem.title: Fragment of noted chant; fragments of legal text, pasted to cardboard

supportDesc.extent: i+205+i; 498 x 354 mm bound to 530 x 420 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto; early foliation in ink using Roman numerals, with some numbers skipped, upper right corner

p.catchwords: Horizontal catchwords in lower margin at folios: 10v; 28v, 38v, 48v, 58v, 68v, 78v, 88v, 98v, 108v, 118v, 128v; vertical catchwords in lower inner margin at folios: 138v, 148v, 158v, 168v, 178v, 188v, 198v

layoutDesc.layout: Musical notation on red, four-line staves; seven staves, with accompanying text, to a page; ruled in grey ink; written area: 363 x 272 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Alternating blue and red penwork initials heightened in purple and red; small pen-flourished initials, alternating blue and red

binding.p: Original wooden boards and diamond pattern tooled leather with metal bosses and corner pieces; leather clasps

history.provenance: According to bookplate on inside front cover, manuscript was presented by "Dr. Wickersham"
